</subSubSection>
</title>
<subSubSection id="0D73263DF99A7CC64A967529C633167B" pageId="null" pageNumber="721" type="description">
<paragraph id="65161FD3CCEB1D6FE222EDFE4CF0F4D3" pageId="null" pageNumber="721">
Die meisten 
<normalizedToken id="148CABAC4DDE4FCCF13F199CBFEAEF2C" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="721">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="9072E864CF53F6A40E5D72D576B08EBF" originalValue="über" pageId="null" pageNumber="721">ueber</normalizedToken>
2 mm breit, 3-8mal so lang wie breit. Innere 
<normalizedToken id="84FE9E9AC886DCEDD67890FDDBD37421" originalValue="Perigonblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="721">Perigonblaetter</normalizedToken>
mit der reifen Frucht nicht verbunden. 
<emphasis id="78832310166C0AADDC2D7AD3243FCE26" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="721">Reife Frucht 1,3</emphasis>
- 
<emphasis id="1513507701142F8F27B1FDB9649791BC" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="721">1,5 mm lang. -</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="BA9DF3B8C34E3DE79176F0422C5B46AA" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="721">Bluete</normalizedToken>
: 
<normalizedToken id="35C2BFE91FFD350BF08A654630022534" originalValue="Später" pageId="null" pageNumber="721">Spaeter</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="DB2AA14BC5E646376CF97B0ED455F0FC" originalValue="Frühling" pageId="null" pageNumber="721">Fruehling</normalizedToken>
bis Herbst.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D23A10F6DFE9F37345BCA0589EB475BA" pageId="null" pageNumber="721">
<emphasis id="0D4DDD0C34DD842700FDDF27A70BCA86" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="721">Zytologische Angaben. 2n = 42</emphasis>
, selten (ca. 9%) 
<emphasis id="48E6B3A1A78F2F514CC0FBB929A688E8" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="721">2n = 41</emphasis>
, sehr selten (ca. 1%) 
<emphasis id="6E7DA0B5BC9EA78FCD30FC0B4032F4DC" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="721">2n = 43:</emphasis>
Material aus Skandinavien, Island und Finnland (
<normalizedToken id="E2D799DD0921496FB529FAC19A82AB74" originalValue="Löve" pageId="null" pageNumber="721">Loeve</normalizedToken>
1944, Sorsa 1962), weitere Angaben in 
<normalizedToken id="9B0F2487126B08BB4CB8FE6EC8FECDEA" originalValue="Löve" pageId="null" pageNumber="721">Loeve</normalizedToken>
und 
<normalizedToken id="4EB61DEF34485DA678AEEC744BCFC71F" originalValue="Löve" pageId="null" pageNumber="721">Loeve</normalizedToken>
(1961).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C0BFAE359887DF1EED7A95102319B9F2" pageId="null" pageNumber="721">
<emphasis id="E4177A2927BBEBA8F6EB44430DF55EF2" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="721">
<pageBreakToken id="941B39B8A072BE7DA59139ABFEE99840" pageId="null" pageNumber="721">Standort</pageBreakToken>
.
</emphasis>
Kollin, montan und subalpin. 
<normalizedToken id="B44CF315AF6492D8C1D5E7768E0E4AB8" originalValue="Nährstoffarme" pageId="null" pageNumber="721">Naehrstoffarme</normalizedToken>
, saure, trockene bis frische, sandige bis lehmige 
<normalizedToken id="CDF63D08F83D03A91C04DF115A331BAA" originalValue="Böden" pageId="null" pageNumber="721">Boeden</normalizedToken>
(Magerkeits- und Versauerungszeiger). 
<normalizedToken id="ADA914FC7C1FAA20AFE5E0325B938ABF" originalValue="Äcker" pageId="null" pageNumber="721">Aecker</normalizedToken>
, Magerwiesen, 
<normalizedToken id="15BD07B5AFF019B8999E9562240C7FD4" originalValue="Waldschläge" pageId="null" pageNumber="721">Waldschlaege</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="5638A5D0E20ABCCB08EE2729E9D5CCE0" originalValue="Wegränder" pageId="null" pageNumber="721">Wegraender</normalizedToken>
, Mauerkronen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7DD07F674400C0C1370DF57203235437" pageId="null" pageNumber="721">
<emphasis id="E2E92C840A653569E2B674EA2A4E7BC1" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="721">Verbreitung. Eurosibirisch-nordamerikanische Pflanze:</emphasis>
Ganz 
<taxonomicName id="F6C03A4199E2BF1DFD2964497B5455E9" authority="Nordafrika" authorityName="Nordafrika" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Europa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="null" pageNumber="721" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Europa, Nordafrika</taxonomicName>
; durch Sibirien zwischen 50 und 65° NB, 
<normalizedToken id="B02C2EB8A60CBFAD02314BDC9CCA7168" originalValue="ostwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="721">ostwaerts</normalizedToken>
bis Kamtschatka und Japan; 
<normalizedToken id="5E9038267BABA632EC707FCBEFA2912E" originalValue="Alëuten" pageId="null" pageNumber="721">Aleuten</normalizedToken>
, Nordamerika (30-60° NB); 
<normalizedToken id="610885DB6D832A59D682ABD2F25BA608" originalValue="Grönland" pageId="null" pageNumber="721">Groenland</normalizedToken>
. Verbreitungskarte von Meusel (1964). - Im Gebiet verbreitet und ziemlich 
<normalizedToken id="10D9BBE87FC293B520BE45873D7043CA" originalValue="häufig" pageId="null" pageNumber="721">haeufig</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
